!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

rescue /ˈrɛskjuː/

(rescuing,rescued,rescues) 

1. V-T If you rescue someone, you get them out of a dangerous or unpleasant situation. 营救 

例： Helicopters rescued nearly 20 people from the roof of the burning building. 直升机从着火的楼顶救出来了将近二十个人。 

2. rescuer N-COUNT 救援者 

例： It took rescuers 90 minutes to reach the trapped men. 救援者们花了90分钟才来到那些被困的男子身边。 

3. N-UNCOUNT Rescue is help which gets someone out of a dangerous or unpleasant situation. 营救 

例： A big rescue operation has been launched for a trawler missing in the North Atlantic. 为了一艘在北大西洋失踪的拖网渔船，已经开始了一项大的营救行动。 

4. N-COUNT A rescue is an attempt to save someone from a dangerous or unpleasant situation. 营救行动 

例： A major air-sea rescue is under way. 一项重要的海空营救行动正在进行中。 

5. PHRASE If you go to someone's rescue or come to their rescue , you help them when they are in danger or difficulty. 营救某人 

例： The 23-year-old's screams alerted a passerby who went to her rescue. 那名23岁女孩的尖叫声引起了一个过路人的警觉，他救了她。

